libchdr_chd: drop the redundant vendored LzmaDec.h include

Companion to patches 0001/0002, and the last hardcoded deps/ reference
on the lzma path. src/libchdr_chd.c includes
"../deps/lzma-25.01/include/LzmaDec.h" a second time at line 76, six
lines after it already pulled in "codec_lzma.h" (which provides
LzmaDec.h itself -- system or vendored, correctly selected by patch
0002). Under WITH_SYSTEM_LZMA this duplicate would re-open the vendored
shim header behind codec_lzma.h's back and re-apply its CHDR_ #define
renames on top of the system declarations.

Deleting it outright (rather than wrapping it in another ifdef) is
correct for both configurations: the file references no Lzma/CLzma/
ISzAlloc/SRes identifier directly -- checked by grepping the whole
translation unit; every LZMA touchpoint goes through the
lzma_codec_init/free/decompress functions declared in codec_lzma.h --
so the include was already dead weight even in the bundled build,
where codec_lzma.h had made the same declarations visible six lines
earlier.

Upstream status: follows the maintainer's own WITH_SYSTEM_* pattern
(added "for distros" per CHANGELOG); candidate for upstreaming, not yet
sent.

diff --git a/src/libchdr_chd.c b/src/libchdr_chd.c
--- a/src/libchdr_chd.c
+++ b/src/libchdr_chd.c
@@ -73,8 +73,6 @@
 #include "../include/libchdr/huffman.h"
 #include "../include/libchdr/macros.h"
 
-#include "../deps/lzma-25.01/include/LzmaDec.h"
-
 #undef TRUE
 #undef FALSE
 #define TRUE 1
